        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 3 at 4:53PM EDT until May 3 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southwest of
Uptown Charlotte, or near Southwest Charlotte, moving northeast at 30
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Freedom Park, Charlotte Douglas Airport, Central Charlotte, Southwest
Charlotte, Steele Creek, Carowinds, Lake Wylie, and South Charlotte.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
